{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout uses a vertical layout for the main content, placing the appbar at the top, followed by product images and details.  Spacing is consistent with the design system's default values.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is designed for a straightforward product detail view. The user can easily view product information and navigate back or add the item to their cart.",
    "componentChoices": "I chose the `appbar` (10:5620) component for the header over `snackbar` (10:3856) and `Bottom navigation` (10:4724) because it's the standard component for top-level page headers. Snackbars are for transient messages, while bottom navigation is for primary screen navigation. The `appbar` provides the needed headline and trailing icons for a product detail view.",
    "componentGaps": "User request requires a carousel component for product images but the design system lacks this component. I created a carousel-like experience using auto-layout horizontal scroll with multiple `IMAGES` components (10:7816). This allows viewing multiple product photos while maintaining semantic meaning.  There is also no dedicated component for displaying product attributes in a list format, therefore I used list item components (10:10214) to achieve the functionality.",
    "visualHierarchy": "The product title is the most prominent element in the `appbar`. Price and description use the appropriate heading and body text styles defined in the system.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "For the `appbar`, I chose `Mode: Light` as it is suitable for the background color of the page. I set `Elevation: flat` as the page needs not to display any elevation. I set `Type: Default` for the main header and selected `trailingIcon1: visible = false` as the back button is unnecessary in this context.  I chose `trailingIcon2: visible = true` and `icon = bookmark` to provide the save/bookmark action which is contextually relevant on the product detail page. For list items, I selected `Condition: 2-line` to properly show product attributes and its values.",
    "nativeElementJustification": "User request requires high quality product images with a smooth scrolling experience, exceeding the capabilities of the single image component. Native image elements within a horizontally scrolling auto-layout provides the needed functionality and UX benefit."
  }
}
```

